										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span class="paragraph">The Crostoli (Chiacchiere, Frappe) are one of the most popular desserts for the days of <a class="underline" title="Carnival in Italy" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carnival_in_Italy">Carnival</a>, which takes different names depending on the region of origin, but which in essence have in common the light pastry dough and a good balance of ingredients.</span></p>
<h2>Enjoy our Crostoli!</h2>

    
<div class="lt-recipe" id="lt-recipe" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Recipe">
    <h4 itemprop="name">Crostoli (Chiacchiere, Frappe)</h4>
        <div class="recipe-info">
                    <div class="publish-date"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="March 21, 2017">March 21, 2017</div> 
                            <div class="servings"><i class="fa fa-user"></i> <label>Servings</label>: 3</div>
                                                <div class="difficulty"><i class="fa fa-tachometer"></i> <label>Difficulty</label>: Easy</div>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-print">
        <a href="javascript:kale_print_recipe('lt-recipe');"><i class="fa fa-print"></i> Print This</a>
    </div>
            <p class="recipe-author">By: <span itemprop="author">italianpot</span></p>
        <div class="recipe-image"><img decoding="async" itemprop="image" src="https://domsites.github.io/italianpot/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/crostoli-High.jpg" alt="Crostoli (Chiacchiere, Frappe)" class="img-responsive" /></div>
        <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-5"><div class="recipe-ingredients">
        <h5>Ingredients</h5>
        <ul>
                        <li itemprop="recipeIngredient">350 gr. Flour</li>
                        <li itemprop="recipeIngredient">50 gr. Sugar</li>
                        <li itemprop="recipeIngredient">50 gr. Butter</li>
                        <li itemprop="recipeIngredient">2/3 spoon Anise or Grappa liqueur</li>
                        <li itemprop="recipeIngredient">Salt</li>
                        <li itemprop="recipeIngredient">Icing sugar</li>
                        <li itemprop="recipeIngredient">oil for frying</li>
                        <li itemprop="recipeIngredient">2 eggs</li>
                    </ul>
    </div></div>
            <div class="col-md-7"><div class="recipe-directions">
        <h5>Directions</h5>
        <ul itemprop="recipeInstructions">
                        <li><span class="step">Step 1</span> Place the flour on the table and in the center the sugar, 1 whole egg and 2 egg yolks, salt, melted butter and anise liqueur or grappa.</li>
                        <li><span class="step">Step 2</span> Knead the dough, form a ball, cover and let rest for 30 minutes. Form a thin sheet with a rolling pin, then with a knife or with the appropriate wheel, get thin strips.</li>
                        <li><span class="step">Step 3</span> Make some incisions in each strip to stick the dough and obtain various forms, or knot them. Fry the crostoli in the oil in small quantities, drain them well and then pass them in powdered sugar.</li>
                    </ul>
    </div></div>
        </div>
</div>
